# notify.local.conf — copy to notify.local.conf here in .claude/hooks/ (gitignored) to enable
# the network push. notify.sh sources it from its own directory, so it must live beside the hook.
# Shell-sourced KEY=value lines. With no file present, notify.sh's network transport is a no-op.

# ntfy (https://ntfy.sh) — the AFK push transport. Set a topic to enable it.
# NTFY_TOPIC=your-secret-topic
# NTFY_URL=https://ntfy.sh        # default; override for a self-hosted server

# Pushover (alternative push provider; wiring is out of scope — config placeholder only).
# PUSHOVER_TOKEN=
# PUSHOVER_USER=
